# Project Libraries

This directory contains project-specific PlatformIO libraries used by the ESP32
firmware.

## Display

Display hardware and graphical screen rendering.

- `display.h` / `display.cpp` define the `Display` hardware service.
- Configures the SPI TFT panel, backlight PWM, and XPT2046 touch device.
- Protects display/touch access with a short mutex because both share SPI.
- Exposes touch reads, backlight control, and controlled access to the LovyanGFX
  device.
- Exposes `displayProbeTouch()` for boot-time XPT2046 diagnostics.
- Tracks the current backlight PWM duty value as an 8-bit brightness level
  from `0` to `255`.
- `graphic_screens.h` / `graphic_screens.cpp` define the UI rendering layer.
- Owns the shared UI palette, day/night theme selection, reusable drawing
  helpers, and the boot, initialization, main-screen, optional CPU-load, and
  battery renderers.
- Exposes `displayBootSetStatus()` so setup can update boot diagnostics without
  reaching into internal `draw*` helpers.

## Input

Local input handling.

- Owns the touch task.
- Uses the XPT2046 IRQ only to wake the task.
- Reads touch coordinates outside the ISR through the Display API.

## Mount

ESP32-to-STM32 mount link.

- Owns `ModbusMaster`, RS485 direction control, and `Serial2` setup.
- Owns the mount command queue and Modbus FreeRTOS task.
- Polls STM32 status/position registers and publishes a mount-state snapshot.
- `mountLinkBegin()` returns whether the STM32 answered the firmware-version
  register with a valid value instead of the disconnected `0xFFFF` value.
- Exposes high-level APIs such as GOTO, STOP, tracking, motors, and jog.

## System

Small system services.

- `system_inputs` is the 1 Hz task for slow board-level inputs.
- Currently samples the active-low night-mode input and refreshes the display
  palette when it changes.
- Contains optional CPU load monitoring behind `ENABLE_CPU_LOAD_MONITOR`.
- When enabled, samples FreeRTOS idle hooks once per second.
- Provides per-core load snapshots for the display header only when the monitor
  is enabled.
- Optionally prints serial runtime diagnostics.

## Telescope

Telescope protocol and configuration support.

- Holds shared firmware configuration constants and pin assignments.
- Provides the `Telescope` state/model used by LX200/Stellarium handling.
- Owns the controller logical clock through `controllerTime`; LX200 date/time
  accessors wrap that same clock so future DS3231 support has a single source
  of truth.
- Includes local WiFi secrets integration through `secrets.h`.

## PlanetCalc

Header-only approximate planetary position calculations.

- `planetcalc.h` computes Sun, Moon, and planet RA/DEC plus auxiliary values
  using Paul Schlyter-style orbital elements.
- Intended for future local object/status calculations without dynamic memory.
